                  <DIV CLASS="global_navigation" ID="nav">
                    <!-- Content Navigation Start -->
                        <h1>BuddySuite</h1>
                        <ul>
                          <li><a href="index.shtml">BuddySuite Home Page</a></li>
                          <li><a href="notice.shtml">Public Domain Notice and Reference</a></li>
                          <li><a href="contact.shtml">Contact Information</a></li>
                        </ul>
                        <!-- Content Navigation End -->
                  </DIV>
	</DIV>

		  <div class="global_content">
		    <!-- Live Content Start -->
            
            <h1>BuddySuite</h1>
            <div class="float_right">
              <a href="https://github.com/biologyguy/BuddySuite/wiki" target="_blank"><img src="images/logo-buddysuite.jpg" width="350" alt=""></a>
            </div>
            <p>The BuddySuite is a collection of four independent, yet interrelated, command line programs that facilitate each step in the workflow of sequence discovery, curation, alignment, and phylogenetic reconstruction. Common sequence, alignment, and tree formats are automatically detected and processed, and many routine manipulations of these files, traditionally performed with an assortment of web tools, bash commands, and/or custom scripts, have been combined into a comprehensive set of toolkits. The suite is written in Python3, is open source, and has been designed for extendability to encourage community involvement with continuing development.</p>
            <p>To minimize the learning curve when adopting the BuddySuite, positional arguments have been kept to a minimum and every tool has been documented in a <a href="https://github.com/biologyguy/BuddySuite/wiki" target="_blank" class="newwin">wiki on GitHub</a>. Each wiki page provides an explanation for any expected parameters as well as use case examples to demonstrate the tools in action.</p>
            <p>BuddySuite is available for all major operating systems (Windows Vista+, Mac OS X, Linux), and can be installed from the Python Package Index using 'pip':</p>
            <pre>
              $: pip install buddysuite
              $: buddysuite -setup
            </pre>
            <p>Alternatively, the entire project can be cloned directly from its <a href="https://github.com/biologyguy/BuddySuite" target="_blank" class="newwin">GitHub repository</a>.</p>
            <p>The following manuscript can be cited if you use BuddySuite in your own work:
              <ul><li>Bond, S.R., Keat, K.E., Barreira, S.N., Baxevanis, A.D. 2017. BuddySuite: Command-Line Toolkits for Manipulating Sequences, Alignments, and Phylogenetic Trees. <em>Mol Biol Evo</em>, 34(6) 1543-1546. [<a href="https://doi.org/10.1093/molbev/msx089" target="_blank" class="newwin">Full Text</a>]</li></ul>
            </p>
            
            <p class="lastmodified">
              Last Modified: Wednesday, 21-Feb-2018 10:29:11 EST
            </p>
